        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Based on the high-level class diagram and the description of the Loan Arranger system, the class Loan is connected to multiple other classes including Bank, Borrower, Bundle, and Loan Arranger, indicating it has multiple responsibilities and interactions.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Image Description: A high-level class diagram of the Loan Arranger system containing four classes: Bank, Loan, Borrower, and Bundle, and another class Loan Arranger. Bank is connected to Loan. Loan is connected to Bank, Borrower, Bundle, and Loan Arranger. Borrower is connected to Loan. Bundle is connected to Loan and Loan Arranger. Loan Arranger is connected to Loan and Bundle.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The class Borrower, on the other hand, is connected only to Loan, suggesting it has fewer responsibilities and less coupling compared to Loan.",
